The paper discusses privacy mechanisms and monetizing private data, which are topics commonly studied in the computer security (cs.CR) and database (cs.DB) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a theoretical framework for assigning prices to query answers, which involves machine learning techniques and information theory, making it relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and information theory (cs.IT) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses micro-payments, which are relevant to the cryptography (cs.CY) sub-category.
